race.comment: AZEOLA (11) beat quite a few of these two starts back over 2050m at Wodonga before another solid effort over this route in a slightly stronger affair last time, working home well for third. Comes back to a BM52 now and draws well. Can bounce back. DASHING DONKEY (1) was second to AZEOLA last time when beaten under a length. He struggles to win but has claims off his last start performance. SECOND NATURE (10) was much better when last seen at Yarra Valley in a 0-56. A repeat of that has him in the mix. PARABELLUM (7) is going okay, not far away of late, beaten 3.5 lengths at Albury in a Bm58 last start. Should prove hard to hold out. MASTER POLANSKI (2) has each-way claims.
